all stimuli in the parafoveal priming experiment are absolute (not relative to screen size)

the cm size of the primes/noprimes was determined by the boundary conditions specified by 
Chartrand & Bargh (1996): 
(2degree visual angle ------Midpoint of Prime at 4degree visual angle --------6degree visual angle)

The position of the primes etc are determined on runtime and depend on the currently 
